The low contraceptive rate might be attributed by fear of side effects, desire for girl/boy child, husbands’ and family (in-law) disapproval, lack of knowledge about contraceptive methods and lack of motivation to use. Education, encouragement of health education programs and involvement of the spouse and in-laws might promote contraceptive utilization in slum dwellers."
