Results
The results showed that the prevalence of low back pain was 74% among operating room personnel. Also, the mean and standard deviation of the participant's awareness of low back pain factors was 24.88 ± 4.18. Also, there was no significant relationship between the prevalence of low back pain and awareness of the personnel about the risk factors of low back pain (p˃0.05).
