Majority of the ambulances 68% (n = 102) were found to have met the standards. Almost 71% (n = 107) of the EMTs were observed to have below average knowledge. Among ambulances not meeting the standards, 66.7% (n = 101) had EMT with below average knowledge. Ambulance quality was found to be independent of the knowledge of EMTs after adjusting for the effects of years of experience and age of the EMTs.
