Results
4.2% had vision impairment (<6/12). 5.2% and 3.2% students residing in urban and rural areas and 4.1% of adolescents and 5.6% of young adults had vision impairment. Gender, place of residence and age groups were significantly associated with visual impairment. Prevalence of various ocular morbidities were bacterial conjunctivitis (0.13%), squint (0.13%), stye (0.1%), conjunctival xerosis (0.1%) and allergic conjunctivitis (0.05%)
