We identified 68 measles case-patients (AR: 11.1%, no death). All sera were positive for IgM measles antibodies. Cases started occurring from 2nd week of September, peaked during October and declined during November. Median age of case-patients was 84 months (IQR: 54–114 months); Vaccine coverage of MCV1 among 9 months to 15 years’ children was 64.8% (379/584) and that of MCV2 among 16 months to 5 years’ children was (62/98) 63.2%. Compared to unvaccinated children, those who received one (RR: 0.16, 95% CI 0.09–0.2) and two doses (RR: 0.09, 95% CI 0.02–0.4) of measles vaccine were at lower risk. The risk of measles was higher among children of religious minority (RR: 28.3, 95% CI 7–114.5). Vaccine Effectiveness of one and two doses of measles vaccine was 83.4% (95% CI 71.2–90.4) and 90.32% (95% CI 59.2–97.7) respectively.
