keywords = "Health insurance, Out of pocket expenditure, Inequality, Economic burden, India",
abstract = "Background
India is one of the most privatised health systems with high OOP payment for health care in the world. The financial burden of OOP payment has an iniquitous effect on access to health care as it restricts health care accessibility among poor. To provide universal health care access to all its citizen government has launched health insurance programs in the recent past.
