Objective
In the present study we detected Influenza and other respiratory viruses in the cases presenting as ILI during a flu epidemic in North India from January to April 2015.
Materials and methods
Total 200 cases, 50 from each month, that were negative for all types of influenza viruses, were randomly selected and tested by Multiplex Real- Time PCR for detection of other respiratory viruses; rhinovirus, adenovirus, Respiratory Syncitial virus (RSV), Human Boca virus (hBoV), Para Influenza viruses 1,2,3, and 4 (PIV 1, PIV 2, PIV 3, PIV 4), measles virus and human Meta Pneumo virus (hMPV).
