keywords = "Isoniazid resistance, Sequencing, Mutation, Tuberculosis",
abstract = "The evolution of resistant TB strain against isoniazid (INH) drug is alarming in the global population. The molecular mechanism of resistance for this compound is found to be associated with mutations in katG and inhA genes. However, types and frequency of mutations vary with geographical region. Therefore, this study aimed to explore new targets of katG and inhA gene mutations and their correlation with isoniazid (INH) minimal inhibitory concentration (MIC) in clinical isolates of Mycobacterium tuberculosis from Uttar Pradesh, India.
