GIS mapping of ADD during the years from 2009–11 identified wards having higher incidence near northern part of Chennai near coastal area. Thus estimation of relative risk using empirical Bayes approach and mapping of disease would help us to estimate accurate incidence despite small observations and to take precautionary measure to prevent and control the spread of the disease."
}
