MTB were detected in all patients in which 17 and 13 isolates were classified as modern and ancient lineage, respectively. Modern lineage was associated with the degree of lung damage (odds ratio [OR]: 3.97; 95% CI: 1.57–6.37), p < 0.001). This lineage was also associated with high TNF-α level (OR: 2.06; 95% CI: 1.31–47.00, p=0.026). In addition, the level of TNF-α was higher in severe compared to mild lung damage cases (p = 0.001).
