A total of 1280 sputum smear-positive patients were enrolled in the study and were subjected for Drug Susceptibility Testing (DST) using First-Line Drugs (FLD's; Rifampicin, Streptomycin, Isoniazid and Ethambutol) using liquid culture DST and Line Probe Assay. These samples were further subjected to second-line drugs DST (ofloxacin and kanamycin) and DNA sequencing to confirm FQ mono-resistance.
Results
The occurrence of FQ mono-resistance among FLD sensitive cases was found to be 3.2% (35/1099). Xpert MTB/RIF assay and rpoB gene sequencing were showed 100% concordance with FLD DST. A total of 35 FQ mono-resistant isolates were further sequenced for gyrA, gyrB and rrs genes. The gene sequencing was found to be in agreement with the DST results for 34 (3.1%) isolates with gyrA and gyrB genes.
