From August 2014 to July 2015, of 196 patients admitted, 152 were included of which 11 (7.2%) expired. On unconditional logistic regression analysis, controlling for abnormal sensorium, cyanosis, and severe acute malnutrition, platelet count <0.7lac/mm3 on admission predicted mortality (adjusted OR=10.7, p<0.03) and had good specificity (95.4%) but low sensitivity (45.5%).
