Treatment with rosuvastatin, in addition to the hypocaloric diet, resulted in a significant decrease in serum periostin levels; ameliorated grades of hepatic steatosis and fibrosis scores, indicating that rosuvastatin, in addition to hypocaloric diet may be effective treatment for NAFLD with dyslipidemia."
