The present population based cross-sectional analysis is performed on the secondary data of India from three rounds of District Level Household Survey (DLHS) conducted in 1998–99, 2002–04 and 2007–08. Indicators for maternal health care utilization are based on full antenatal check up (FANC) as defined by RCH program and skilled institutional delivery attendance (SID) as defined by WHO by the mode of service provider (Public vs Private). Multinomial logistic regression was used for statistical analysis by considering these indicators as the outcome variables treating various socio-demographic factors as independent variables.
