Finding
Districts in which community-based DOTS was implemented showed better median treatment success rate (92.88%) than facility-based DOTS implemented districts (89.84%) (p = 0.02). The median loss to follow up the rate of community-based DOTS implemented districts (0.92%) was better than the median loss to follow uprate of facility-based DOTS implemented districts (2.967%) (p = 0.02).
