Results
The average age of participants (69.9% male) was 59.3 ± 9.1. The analysis suggested three clusters: (i) patients with medium distress and weak participation, (ii) patients with mild distress and average participation, and (iii) patients with medium distress and good participation. While there was no significant difference among the clusters with regards to healthy behaviors and mortality rate, the difference was significant with regards to psychological distress, somatic symptoms, duration and quality of sleep, and general quality of life (P < 0.05).
