Initial distress and weak participation of outpatients in CR has more severe long-term somatic and psychological consequences. Screening of increased psychological distress and identification of candidates for failure to adhere to CR at the baseline are considered among the most important responsibilities of the CR team."
}
@article{SITEPU2020113,
title = "Epidemiological investigation of chikungunya outbreak, West Kalimantan, Indonesia",
