Results
During 20 July to 25 September 2015, a total of 28 measles cases were identified with no death. All tested blood samples were positive for measles-specific IgM antibodies confirming the outbreak. All cases presented with fever and rash; cough (80%), coryza (65%), and conjunctivitis (25%). The attack rate (AR) was 14.1% (age ranged between 1 and 14 years old), the highest AR (50.0%) occurred among those aged 1–4 years. In multivariate model, those who have not received measless vaccication and those who had contact with a measles case had higher odds of having infection, with adjusted odds ratio (aOR): 2.31 (95%CI: 1.22–4.27) and aOR: 1.15 (95%CI: 1.12–3.70), respectively.
