Methods
Articles reporting the data of lag time between the symptom onset of Chikungunya or Zika and GBS were included for pooled analysis. Maximum likelihood estimation was adopted to estimate the incubation period distribution of GBS conditioned to that of the antecedent infection.
Results
A total of 89 Chikungunya- and Zika-related GBS cases from 23 articles were identified. The incubation period distribution of GBS is lognormal distributed with the median of 13–14 days and does not depend on the antecedent infection.
