Allergic rhinitis (AR) and bronchial asthma (AS) are two related clinical types of allergic respiratory diseases, and there is a necessity to define both allergies in terms of the associated allergens. Accordingly, a cross-sectional observational study was conducted to examine the allergen profile in AR and AS of Iraqi patients, in whom the data are not well-elaborated.
