The 16–45 years was the most encountered age group in AR and AS patients (79.1 and 75.1%, respectively). For total IgE, AS patients at all age groups had a significantly higher level than in AR cases of both genders. However, total IgE level showed no significant variation between age groups with the exception of total AS patients in the age group >45 years who had the lowest IgE level (338 ± 269 IU/ml). Screening the sera for eight allergen types (animal dander, grasses, house dust, insects, mites, molds, trees and weeds) depicted that molds were the most frequent allergen in AR and AS patients (8.7 and 19.6%, respectively), but mixed sources of allergens were much more frequently encountered.
