Among 50 subjects of type-1 diabetes included in the study, median annual cost of care for was 25,758/- and of this 90.9% direct and 9.1% was indirect cost. There was a negative correlation between cost of care and glycemic control. The spending on diabetes care was lower among the subjects with psychosocial illnesses. The quality of life was poor among subjects who spend less on diabetes care.
