The frequency percentage of patients with osteopenia and osteoporosis in the Tenofovir group (60.43%) was significantly more than that of the control group (21.43%) (P < 0.05). Among Tenofovir group, 51.02% of males and 42.22% of females had osteopenia. Also, 14.28% of males and 15.56% of females had osteoporosis. In the patients who had consumed more time, incidence of osteoporosis and osteopenia were reported more often (P > 0.05). Among patients with osteopenia, 85.71% of the patients in the hip region and 44.44% of them in the lumber area had decreased bone density. Also, osteoporosis was more reported in hip (90.48%), lumbar (90.48%) and femoral neck (80.95%) respectively.
